      "content": "```markdown\n# CloudScale API Documentation\n\n## Overview\nWelcome to the CloudScale API documentation. This guide will help you understand the various endpoints available, including the `GET /user` endpoint.\n\n## Authentication\nBefore accessing any endpoints, ensure you are authenticated. The `GET /user` endpoint requires a valid authentication token.\n\n## Endpoints\n\n### `GET /user`\nThis endpoint retrieves the profile information for the authenticated user.\n\n#### Request\n- Method: GET\n- Endpoint: `/user`\n- Headers: `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n\n#### Response\n- Status Code: 200 OK\n- Body: JSON containing user profile information\n\n## Error Handling\nIn case of errors, the API will return appropriate status codes and messages to help you troubleshoot.\n\n## Rate Limiting\nPlease adhere to the rate limits to ensure fair usage and avoid service disruptions.\n\n## Contact Us\nFor support, please contact our helpdesk at [support@cloudscale.com](mailto:support@cloudscale.com).\n\n## Contributing\nWe welcome contributions to improve our API documentation. Please follow our contribution guidelines.\n\n## License\nThis documentation is licensed under the MIT License.\n```\n\nThis version includes all the necessary structural sections (h1 and h",
